Hecto App - Product Requirements Document
=========================================

## Data Structure

User (personal identity)
→ belongs to Company (commercial identity)
→ Company holds Subscription
→ Company owns Campaigns
→ Campaign owns Pitches
→ Pitches spawn Negotiations / Messages

This avoids every future permission conflict.

---

## Information Architecture (Phase 1)

### 1. Dashboard (Command Centre)
**Summary Stats Row:**
- Active Campaigns
- Pending Pitches
- Needs Reply
- Completed Deals

**Action Toolbar:**
- New Campaign button
- New Pitch button
- Filter controls
- Export

**Horizontal Tabs:**
- All
- My Campaigns
- Incoming Pitches
- Needs Attention

**Main Content:**
- Data table (desktop) / Card list (mobile)
- Status badges: Draft (gray), Active (blue), Needs Reply (orange), Accepted (green), Declined (red)

### 2. Campaigns
Company-level list with filters:
- Active
- Draft
- Closed

**Campaign Detail View:**
- Horizontal tabs: Overview, Pitches, Settings
- Inbound pitches list with status and controls

### 3. Pitches
Combined outgoing/incoming view, filtered by:
- Sent
- Received
- Needs Reply
- Accepted
- Declined

### 4. Messages / Negotiations
- Threaded inbox (left panel)
- Active thread (center)
- AI query panel (right on desktop, bottom sheet on mobile)
- Each thread tied to a pitch
- Declining closes thread

### 5. Profile & Company Settings
**User:** name, email, photo
**Company:** logo, URL, vertical, subscription status, billing

